# Force LF on shell scripts and hooks regardless of a checkout's core.autocrlf
# setting. CRLF breaks a shebang's interpreter lookup under real Linux
# (`/bin/sh^M: bad interpreter`) and bash's backslash line-continuation -- both
# confirmed empirically in this fleet 2026-07-14; see runtime/.gitattributes and
# media-generation/.gitattributes for the write-ups. Both patterns are PROACTIVE
# here: contracts tracks no .sh file and no hook as of 2026-07-23, so they pin
# nothing that exists yet -- they exist so the first one added is covered without
# a second pass.
#
# Deliberately narrow. No `* text=auto` and no rules over `gen/` : this repo's
# generated bindings are consumed by version pin, and a blanket normalization
# could rewrite generated output and change what an already-pinned consumer sees
# from a tag. Nothing here touches a schema or requires a version bump.
.gitattributes text eol=lf
*.sh text eol=lf
.githooks/pre-commit text eol=lf
